  <bioghist id="aspace_0f97e756c019a677b533fb678d99cf8f">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Originally sent as recruiting tools to the College of Architecture, Art, and Planning.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_2f419d8132cb856628a6accd1e524ef7">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Brochures from architectural firms showcasing their work. Firms include Amenta/Emma, Bowie Gridley Architects, Burt Hill Kosar Rittelmann Associates, The Design Alliance, EYP Mission Critical Facilities, Inc., Hellmuth, Obata + Kassabaum, Hillier Architecture, HOLT Architects, Mancini Duffy, McCall Design Group, Michael Graves Architects, Odell, Perkins Eastman Architects, Simon Martin Vegue Winkelstein Moris.</p><p> Also, "A Proposal for a branch bank of The City National Bank and Trust Company, Gloversville, New York," Edgar Tafel Architect, n.d.; "Schematic Presentation for Atlantic City Performing Arts Center," Taliesin Associated Architects of the Frank Lloyd Wright Foundation, William Wesley Peters, Architect, 1975.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_c511b02d3fec6773df19ed2b7f11044e">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Architects' brochures, #8051. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
